oadwayworld.com/article/Breaking-THE-PROM-AINT-TOO-PROUD-BEETLEJUICE-More-Earn-Drama-League-Awards-Nominations-20190417 |website=BroadwayWorld |accessdate=May 1, 2019 |date=April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Gary: A Sequel to Titus Andronicus''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''[[To Kill a Mockingbird (2018 play)|To Kill a Mockingbird]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''[[King Lear]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Outstanding Revival of a Play\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''The Waverly Gallery''\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n===[[Lucille Lortel Award]]s===\n{| class=wikitable width=90%\n! width=3%| Year\n! width=27%| Nominated work\n! width=56%| Category\n! width=9%| Result\n! width=5%|{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''Red Light Winter''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Outstanding Play\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Previous Nominees and Recipients: 2006|url=http://www.lortelaward.com/2006nominees.htm|publisher=The Lucille Lortel Awards|accessdate=January 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808152148/http://www.lortelaward.com/2006nominees.htm|archive-date=August 8, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2013\t\n| ''Cock''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Previous Nominees and Recipients: 2013|url=http://www.lortelaward.com/2013nominees.htm|publisher=The Lucille Lortel Awards|accessdate=January 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180208141143/http://www.lortelaward.com/2013nominees.htm|archive-date=February 8, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Every Brilliant Thing''\n| Outstanding Solo Show\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Previous Nominees and Recipients: 2015|url=http://www.lortelaward.com/2015nominees.htm|publisher=The Lucille Lortel Awards|accessdate=January 29, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===[[Outer Critics Circle Award]]s===\n{| class=wikitable width=90%\n! width=3%| Year\n! width=27%| Nominated work\n! width=56%| Category\n! width=9%| Result\n! width=5%|{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=