e Lightning]] || 69.6% (119/171)\n|-\n| [[Three-point field goal|3-pt field goal]] percentage || [[Adrian Majstrovich]] || [[Kalamunda Eastern Suns]] || 45.7% (64/140)\n|-\n| [[Free throw]] percentage || Bryce Burch || [[Cockburn Cougars]] || 83.6% (122/146)\n|}\n\n===Regular season===\n* '''Most Valuable Player:''' Luke Meyer (Geraldton Buccaneers)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://websites.sportstg.com/assoc_page.cgi?c=1-5011-0-444185-0&sID=78732&&news_task=DETAIL&articleID=9987405 |title=2009 SBL Award Winners |work=SportsTG.com |date=11 September 2009 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404085948/https://websites.sportstg.com/assoc_page.cgi?c=1-5011-0-444185-0&sID=78732&news_task=DETAIL&articleID=9987405 |archivedate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n* '''Coach of the Year:''' [[Andy Stewart (basketball)|Andy Stewart]] (Lakeside Lightning)\n* '''Most Improved Player:''' [[Ben Purser]] (Perry Lakes Hawks)\n* '''All-Star Five:'''\n** '''PG:''' Shamus Ballantyne (Goldfields Giants)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://websites.sportstg.com/assoc_page.cgi?c=1-5011-0-444185-0&sID=78732&&news_task=DETAIL&articleID=9987414 |title=SBL All Star Teams 2009 |work=SportsTG.com |date=11 September 2009 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026163113/https://websites.sportstg.com/assoc_page.cgi?c=1-5011-0-444185-0&sID=78732&&news_task=DETAIL&articleID=9987414 |archivedate=26 October 2017}}</ref>\n** '''SG:''' [[Luke Payne]] (Lakeside Lightning)\n** '''SF:''' Luke Meyer (Geraldton Buccaneers)\n** '''PF:''' [[Adrian Majstrovich]] (Kalamunda Eastern Suns)\n** '''C:''' [[Jarrad Prue]] (Lakeside Lightning)\n\n===Finals===\n* '''Grand Final MVP:''' [[Luke Payne]] (Lakeside Lightning)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://websites.sportstg.com/assoc_page.cgi?c=11-5011-0-83917-0&sID=78732&&news_task=DETAIL&articleID=9841367 |title=Tigers break Magic's spell |work=SportsTG.com |date=25 August 2009 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111091928/https:/